<span id="freeTextContainer10868540558397553829">Sometimes there are books that take all the joy of reading away, but for one reason or another, you feel you need to finish them. This is one of those books for me. Written by one of my favorite apostles, about an amazing subject, I figured this book would be perfect and I tried to see it through to the end. <br/><br/>Unfortunately, I couldn&apos;t finish. I really couldn&apos;t handle a book that was basically a list of scriptures about Christ, with very little meat to it. It&apos;s like a junior version of Jesus the C</span>
  <span id="freeText10868540558397553829" style="display:none">Sometimes there are books that take all the joy of reading away, but for one reason or another, you feel you need to finish them. This is one of those books for me. Written by one of my favorite apostles, about an amazing subject, I figured this book would be perfect and I tried to see it through to the end. <br /><br />Unfortunately, I couldn't finish. I really couldn't handle a book that was basically a list of scriptures about Christ, with very little meat to it. It's like a junior version of Jesus the Christ, without Talmage's epic insights. </span>
